# OmniHammer Weapon Family Style Guide

*Design reference for maintaining weapon identity and consistency across all codexes.*

This document codifies the signature rules, baseline stats, and scaling conventions for every weapon technology family in OmniHammer. When writing weapon profiles for any codex, consult this guide to ensure that a player can look at a weapon's family name and immediately know what rules to expect.

This is an informal convention document, not a rules chapter. Individual weapons may add rules on top of their family signature, but should never lack the family baseline unless there is a deliberate, documented reason.

---

## MELEE WEAPON FAMILIES

### 1. Chain Weapons

**Signature Rule:** ***Shred*** (re-roll failed To Wound rolls)

**Identity:** Motorized teeth that rip and tear through flesh and armor. The chain mechanism is what earns Shred — re-rolling wounds represents the sawing action finding purchase.

| Weapon | S | AP | Additional Rules | Notes |
| :---- | :---: | :---: | :---- | :---- |
| Chainsword | User | — | — | Basic chain weapon. |
| Chainaxe | User | 4 | — | Heavier head, better AP. |
| Chainfist | ×2 | 2 | Power Weapon, Armorbane, Specialist Weapon, Unwieldy | Chain + power field hybrid. Armorbane from the powered sawing action. |
| Kill Saw | ×2 | 2 | Specialist Weapon, Unwieldy | Ork paired buzzsaws. Trades Power Weapon for raw Shred consistency. |
| Dread Klaw | ×2 | 2 | Power Weapon, Specialist Weapon | Walker-scale chain/power hybrid. |
| Dread Saw | ×2 | 3 | Specialist Weapon | Walker-scale saw. |
| Mega-Choppa | ×2 | 1 | Terrible Weapon, Two-Handed | Gargant-scale. Adds Terrible Weapon at the extreme top end. |
| Reaper Chainsword | ×2 (max 10) | 3 | — | Knight-scale. Superheavy chain weapon. |
| Khornate Eviscerator | ×2 | 2 | Two-Handed, Unwieldy, Armorbane | Chaos two-handed chainsword. |

**Scaling Pattern:** AP improves and additional rules accumulate as the weapon scales up, but ***Shred*** is always present. Chain weapons paired with power fields (Chainfist, Dread Klaw) gain ***Power Weapon*** and/or ***Armorbane*** on top of Shred.

**Factions:** Imperium (all), Chaos, Orks (Kill Saw, Dread Saw, Mega-Choppa).

---

### 2. Power Weapons

**Signature Rule:** ***Power Weapon*** USR + **AP 2**

**Identity:** A disruption field generator that destabilizes molecular bonds on contact. The energy field is what earns the Power Weapon USR. AP 2 is universal across the family.

| Variant | S | Additional Rules | Notes |
| :---- | :---: | :---- | :---- |
| Power Sword | User | — | Balanced, no drawbacks. |
| Power Axe | +1 | Unwieldy | Extra S, slower swing. |
| Power Maul | +2 | Concussive | Blunt trauma, stuns targets. |
| Power Spear | +1 on charge / User after | — | Rewards aggressive charging. |
| Power Fist / Klaw | ×2 | Unwieldy, Specialist Weapon | Maximum S, slowest swing. |
| Lightning Claw | User | Shred, Specialist Weapon | Speed and lethality over brute force. Shred from multiple raking blades. |

**Scaling Pattern:** All power weapons share AP 2 and the Power Weapon USR. Variants trade between Strength, Initiative (Unwieldy), and secondary effects (Concussive, Shred). Heavier variants gain Specialist Weapon.

**Factions:** Universal (Imperium, Chaos, Orks, Eldar variants).

**Note on Imperial Guard:** The IG wargear list has some power weapons at AP 3 (Power Sword) and AP 4 (Power Maul). These should be reviewed for consistency with the AP 2 family standard, or deliberately documented as lower-quality Guard-issue variants.

---

### 3. Force Weapons

**Signature Rule:** ***Force*** USR (includes ***Power Weapon***)

**Identity:** A power weapon that a psyker can push into massive wounds by channeling warp energy. Force inherently includes Power Weapon, so all force weapons function as power weapons with the additional psychic activation.

**Variant Structure:** Mirrors power weapons — Force Sword, Force Axe, Force Stave follow the same S/AP/additional rules pattern as their power weapon equivalents, plus the Force USR.

**Factions:** Imperium (Librarians, Grey Knights), Chaos (Sorcerers), Eldar (Warlocks), Orks (Weirdboy Staff).

