## RANGED WEAPON FAMILIES — IMPERIUM STANDARD

### 4. Bolt Weapons

**Signature Rule:** None (stat-defined family)

**Identity:** Mass-reactive explosive projectiles. Reliable, no-frills, the workhorse of Imperial warfare. Their identity is the stat baseline, not a USR.

| Weapon | Range | S | AP | Type | Notes |
| :---- | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---- | :---- |
| Bolt Pistol | 12" | 4 | 5 | Pistol 1 | Baseline. |
| Boltgun | 24" | 4 | 5 | Rapid Fire 1 | Baseline. |
| Storm Bolter | 24" | 4 | 5 | Assault 2 | Twin-barrel, faster fire. |
| Combi-Bolter | 24" | 4 | 5 | Rapid Fire, Twin-Linked | Chaos twin-barrel variant. |
| Heavy Bolter | 36" | 5 | 4 | Heavy 3 | **Scaled up:** +1S, +1AP, longer range. |
| Vulcan Mega-Bolter | 60" | 6 | 3 | Heavy 15 | **Scaled up further:** +2S, +2AP from baseline. |

**Baseline:** S4 AP5. Heavy variants scale S and AP upward (+1 per size tier).

**Factions:** Imperium (all), Chaos, Orks (Looted 'Umie Bolter).

---

### 5. Las Weapons

**Signature Rule:** None (stat-defined family)

**Identity:** Focused energy beams. Clean, reliable, scales linearly with power output. The most common weapon technology in the Imperium.

| Weapon | Range | S | AP | Type | Notes |
| :---- | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---- | :---- |
| Laspistol | 12" | 3 | — | Pistol | Bottom of the ladder. |
| Lasgun | 24" | 3 | — | Rapid Fire | Standard infantry weapon. |
| Hot-Shot Laspistol | 6" | 3 | 3 | Pistol | Trades range for AP. |
| Hot-Shot Lasgun | 18" | 3 | 3 | Rapid Fire | Trades range for AP. |
| Multi-laser | 36" | 6 | 6 | Heavy 3 | Mid-tier vehicle weapon. |
| Lascannon | 48" | 9 | 2 | Heavy 1 | Top of the ladder. |

**Scaling Pattern:** S3 → S6 → S9. AP improves from — to 6 to 2. Hot-Shot variants sacrifice range for AP at the same Strength tier. The ladder is clean and predictable.

**Factions:** Imperium (primarily Imperial Guard, also Space Marines for Lascannon).

---

### 6. Flamer Weapons

**Signature Rule:** ***Template*** delivery

**Identity:** Projected streams of burning liquid or gas. Every flamer uses the teardrop template. Template weapons auto-hit and ignore cover per core rules — that IS the family rule.

| Weapon | S | AP | Type | Notes |
| :---- | :---: | :---: | :---- | :---- |
| Hand Flamer | 3 | 6 | Pistol | Compact sidearm variant. |
| Flamer | 4 | 5 | Assault 1 | Standard infantry flamer. |
| Heavy Flamer | 5 | 4 | Assault 1 | Larger fuel tank, hotter burn. |
| Inferno Cannon | 6 | 4 | Heavy 1, Torrent | Vehicle-mounted. Torrent extends placement range. |
| Skorcha (Ork) | 6 | 4 | Heavy 1 | Ork heavy flamer equivalent. |
| Burna (Ork) | 4 | 5 | Assault 1 | Ork standard flamer equivalent. |

**Scaling Pattern:** S3/AP6 → S4/AP5 → S5/AP4 → S6/AP4. Each size tier gains +1S and +1AP (up to a ceiling). Vehicle-mounted flamers gain ***Torrent*** at the top end.

**Factions:** Universal. Ork variants (Skorcha, Burna) follow the same scaling.

