## RANGED WEAPON FAMILIES — TAU / VOTANN

### 17. Pulse Weapons (Tau)

**Signature Rule:** None (stat-defined family)

**Identity:** Tau standard-issue directed-energy weapons. Reliable, slightly above Imperial baseline. Their identity is the S5 AP5 stat block.

| Weapon | Range | S | AP | Type | Notes |
| :---- | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---- | :---- |
| Pulse Pistol | 12" | 5 | 5 | Pistol | Baseline. |
| Pulse Carbine | 18" | 5 | 5 | Assault 2 | Shorter range, more shots. |
| Pulse Rifle | 28" | 5 | 5 | Rapid Fire | Standard Fire Warrior weapon. |
| Pulse Blaster | Variable | 5–6 | 3–5 | Assault | Variable profile by range bracket. |
| Longshot Pulse Rifle | 48" | 5 | 5 | Heavy 1, Sniper | Extended barrel, adds Sniper. |

**Baseline:** S5 AP5. Range and type vary by role. The Pulse Blaster is the exception — variable profile by distance, but still rooted in pulse technology.

**Factions:** Tau Empire.

---

### 18. Ion Weapons (Tau / Votann)

**Signature Rule:** **Overcharge mode** (+1S, ***Gets Hot***)

**Identity:** Dual-mode energy weapons. Standard mode is safe and reliable; Overcharge pushes the reactor for more power at the risk of catastrophic failure. The dual-profile structure IS the family rule.

| Weapon | Range | Standard S/AP | Overcharge S/AP | Notes |
| :---- | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---- |
| Cyclic Ion Blaster | 18" | S7 AP4, Assault 3 | S8 AP4, Assault 3, Gets Hot | — |
| Ion Rifle | 30" | S7 AP4, Heavy 1 | S8 AP4, Heavy 1, Blast, Gets Hot | Overcharge adds Blast. |
| Ion Cannon | 60" | S7 AP3, Heavy 3 | S8 AP3, Heavy 1, Large Blast, Gets Hot | Overcharge adds Large Blast. |
| Ion Accelerator | 72" | S8 AP2, Heavy 3 | S9 AP2, Heavy 1, Large Blast, Gets Hot | Overcharge adds Large Blast. |

**Scaling Pattern:** S and AP improve with weapon size. Overcharge always adds +1S and Gets Hot. Heavy Ion weapons typically gain Blast or Large Blast on Overcharge, trading volume for area effect.

**Shared Technology:** Ion weapons are shared between Tau and Leagues of Votann. The Kin likely originated the technology. Votann variants may have superior stat profiles but follow the same family conventions.

**Factions:** Tau Empire, Leagues of Votann.

---

### 19. Rail Weapons (Tau / Votann)

**Signature Rule:** ***Armorbane*** + **AP1** + high Strength

**Identity:** Hypervelocity kinetic penetrators launched via electromagnetic acceleration. They punch through anything. AP1 is universal, Armorbane (2D6 armor penetration) ensures even the heaviest armor is unreliable protection.

| Weapon | Range | S | AP | Type | Notes |
| :---- | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---- | :---- |
| Rail Rifle | 30" | 6 | 1 | Heavy 1, Armorbane | Man-portable. |
| Heavy Rail Rifle | 60" | 8 | 1 | Heavy 2, Armorbane | Broadside weapon. |
| Railgun (Solid) | 72" | 10 | 1 | Heavy 1, Armorbane, Terrible Weapon | Hammerhead main gun. Terrible Weapon at top end. |
| Magna Rail Rifle | TBD | TBD | 1 | TBD, Armorbane | Shared Tau/Votann next-gen variant. |

**Scaling Pattern:** S scales dramatically (6 → 8 → 10). AP1 and Armorbane are constant. The Railgun adds Terrible Weapon at the superheavy tier.

**Known Inconsistency:** Current Tau codex rail weapon profiles do not carry Armorbane. This must be added during the Tau update pass.

**Shared Technology:** See Ion Weapons note. Rail technology is shared between Tau and Leagues of Votann.

**Factions:** Tau Empire, Leagues of Votann.

