## RANGED WEAPON FAMILIES — ELDAR

### 20. Shuriken Weapons (Craftworld Eldar)

**Signature Rule:** ***Rending*** + **S4 AP5 baseline**

**Identity:** Mono-molecular crystal discs fired at extreme velocity. Normally comparable to bolt weapons in raw output, but the monomolecular edge occasionally finds a seam in any armor. Rending provides a high ceiling — wound roll of 6 = auto-wound at AP2.

| Weapon | Range | S | AP | Type | Notes |
| :---- | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---- | :---- |
| Shuriken Pistol | ~12" | 4 | 5 | Pistol, Rending | Baseline. |
| Shuriken Catapult | ~12–18" | 4 | 5 | Assault, Rending | Standard Guardian weapon. |
| Dire Avenger Catapult | ~18" | 4 | 5 | Assault, Rending | Extended range variant. |
| Shuriken Cannon | ~24–36" | 6 | 5 | Heavy/Assault, Rending | Scaled up S. |

**Baseline:** S4 AP5, matching bolt weapons. Shuriken Cannon scales to S6 but keeps AP5 — the discs get bigger but don't inherently penetrate heavier armor (that's what Rending is for).

**Factions:** Craftworld Eldar, Harlequins, Corsairs.

---

### 21. Distortion / D-Weapons (Eldar)

**Signature Rule:** ***Terrible Weapon*** + **AP 1–2**

**Identity:** Warp-rift weapons that tear holes in reality. Anything caught in the breach has chunks of itself removed or is shunted into the warp. Terrible Weapon (D3 damage per hit, re-roll vehicle damage) reflects the catastrophic, reality-breaking nature of each hit.

**Members:** Wraithcannon, D-Scythe, D-Cannon, Hemlock weaponry. High S, AP 1–2, Terrible Weapon. Individual weapons may add Blast or Template.

**Factions:** Craftworld Eldar (Wraithguard, Wraithknight, Hemlock).

---

### 22. Bright Lance

**Individual weapon, not a family.** Carries ***Lance*** (treat vehicle armor >12 as 12). The Lance USR is shared cross-faction with Dark Eldar Dark Lances. Bright Lances are the Eldar anti-heavy-armor tool.

---

### 23. Scatter Laser

**Individual weapon, not a family.** Carries ***Laser Lock*** (hits from this weapon make other weapons on the same model Twin-Linked for the rest of the phase). High volume suppression weapon.

