## RANGED WEAPON FAMILIES — NECRONS

### 26. Gauss Weapons (Necrons)

**Signature Rule:** ***Disintegrating Beam***

**Identity:** Atom-by-atom molecular disassembly. Gauss weapons can theoretically damage anything given enough time. Disintegrating Beam (wound roll of 6 auto-wounds regardless of T; armor pen roll of 6 auto-glances vehicles) represents this — even a humble Gauss Flayer can scratch a Land Raider.

**Baseline:** S5 AP4, scaling up with weapon size. Note this is slightly superior to bolt weapons (S4 AP5) — Necron standard issue outperforms Imperial standard issue at the basic level.

**Factions:** Necrons.

---

### 27. Tesla Weapons (Necrons)

**Signature Rule:** ***Tesla*** USR

**Identity:** Arcing electrical discharge that jumps between targets. Volume of fire weapons that become devastating when the lightning starts chaining.

**Tesla USR (NEW):**

> ***Tesla:*** When firing a weapon with this special rule, each To Hit roll of 6 generates one additional automatic hit on the target. For each bonus hit generated, roll a D6; on a further 6, another bonus hit is generated. Continue rolling until no further 6s are rolled.

**Members:** Tesla Carbine, Tesla Cannon, Tesla Destructor. Stats TBD with Necron codex.

**Factions:** Necrons.

---

### 28. Particle Weapons (Necrons)

**Signature Rule:** ***Ignores Cover***

**Identity:** Anti-matter particle streams that saturate an area. The particles are so numerous and fine that hiding behind cover provides no protection — the air itself becomes lethal.

**Members:** Particle Whip, Particle Beamer, Particle Caster, Particle Shredder. Stats TBD with Necron codex.

**Factions:** Necrons.

---

### 29. Transdimensional Weapons (Necrons)

**Signature Rule:** ***Warp Displacement***

**Identity:** Phase-shifting weapons that briefly shunt targets through dimensional space and rematerialize them nearby — often inside solid objects. The Warp Displacement USR (already defined in OmniHammer) represents this perfectly.

**Members:** Transdimensional Beamer. Stats TBD with Necron codex.

**Factions:** Necrons. Also used by Ork Shokka/Tellyport weapons.

---

### 30. Doomsday / Death Ray (Necrons)

**Signature Rule:** ***Terrible Weapon***

**Identity:** Necron super-heavy energy weapons of catastrophic destructive power. Each hit is a reality-ending event for the target. Not a broad family — these are individual super-weapons that share the Terrible Weapon identity.

**Members:** Doomsday Cannon, Death Ray. Stats TBD with Necron codex.

**Factions:** Necrons.

---

## RANGED WEAPON FAMILIES — CHAOS

### 31. Daemon Weapons (Chaos)

**Signature Rule:** **Mastery Test** (roll D6 at start of Assault Phase, add to Attacks)

**Identity:** Weapons containing bound daemons that surge with chaotic power. Already fully written in the Chaos codex. Individual daemon weapons add unique effects on top of the Mastery Test.

**Factions:** Chaos (all marks).

---

### 32. Plague Weapons (Nurgle)

**Signature Rule:** ***Poison (4+)*** baseline

**Identity:** Diseased, corroding, toxin-dripping weapons blessed by the Plague God. They bypass conventional toughness through viral payload. Poison (4+) is the family floor — more potent relics may escalate to Poison (3+) or (2+).

**Members:** Plague Sword, Plague Knife, Blight Grenades, Pandemic Staff, and others. Individual weapons may add additional effects (Plague Swords may gain persistent disease effects when defined).

**Factions:** Chaos (Nurgle-marked units, Death Guard).

---

### 33. Warpflame Weapons (Tzeentch)

**Signature Rule:** ***Template*** + ***Soul Blaze***

**Identity:** Daemonic fire that burns the soul. These are flamers, but the fire doesn't go out. Template provides the delivery; Soul Blaze (persistent D3 S4 AP5 hits, 4+ to persist each turn) provides the lingering burn. Regular flamers are Template only; warpflamers add Soul Blaze.

**Members:** Warpflamer, Baleflamers, Breath of Chaos, and similar.

**Factions:** Chaos (Tzeentch daemons, Thousand Sons).

---

## RANGED WEAPON FAMILIES — SLAANESH

### 34. Sonic Weapons (Slaanesh)

**Signature Rule:** ***Ignores Cover*** + ***Strikedown***

**Identity:** Weaponized hypersonics that bypass physical barriers (Ignores Cover — sound goes through walls) and physically stagger targets (Strikedown — wounded models move as if in difficult terrain, even if the wound is saved). The victims are disoriented, their inner ears scrambled, muscles spasming.

**Members:** Sonic Blaster, Blastmaster, Doom Siren. Individual weapons add delivery-specific rules (Doom Siren is Template, Blastmaster is Blast/Heavy).

**Factions:** Chaos (Slaanesh, Noise Marines).

