## RANGED WEAPON FAMILIES — TYRANIDS

### 38. Bio-Plasma (Tyranid)

**Signature Rule:** ***Gets Hot*** + **AP 2** (follows Plasma family convention)

**Identity:** Organic plasma analogue — superheated bio-acid generated internally. Gets Hot represents the creature straining its bio-plasma organ to the point of self-injury. Follows the Imperial plasma family convention for intuitive cross-faction recognition.

**Factions:** Tyranids.

---

### 39. Creature-Delivery Weapons (Tyranid)

**Signature Rule:** ***Infestation***

**Identity:** Living ammunition — beetles, maggots, borer organisms fired at the enemy. The creatures cause immediate damage and continue to gnaw and infest afterward. The Infestation USR was specifically designed for this application (created in the Ork codex with Tyranid cross-faction use explicitly flagged).

**Members:** Fleshborer, Devourer, and similar bio-organism delivery weapons.

**Factions:** Tyranids. Also used by Ork Squig Launchas and Gretzookas.

---

### 40. Bio-Acid Weapons (Tyranid)

**Signature Rule:** ***Template*** (follows Flamer family convention)

**Identity:** Organic flamer analogue — projected streams of bio-acid that dissolve on contact. Uses the template as delivery. The acid replaces promethium but the battlefield effect is identical.

**Members:** Pyro-acid spray and similar. Stats TBD with Tyranid codex.

**Factions:** Tyranids.

---

### 41. Bio-Electric Weapons (Tyranid)

**Signature Rule:** ***Tesla*** USR

**Identity:** Organic tesla analogue — bio-generated electrical discharge that arcs between targets. Follows the Tesla family convention (originally Necron, but the biological equivalent functions identically).

**Members:** Electroshock Grubs, Thorax bio-electric, and similar.

**Factions:** Tyranids.

---

### 42. Stranglethorn / Barbed Weapons (Tyranid)

**Signature Rule:** ***Pinning*** + ***Strikedown***

**Identity:** Seed pods that burst into entangling, constricting vines on impact. The vines grab you (Pinning — forces a Pinning Test) and drag you down (Strikedown — move as if in difficult terrain next turn). Area denial through biological entanglement.

**Members:** Barbed Strangler, Stranglethorn Cannon.

**Factions:** Tyranids.

---

### 43. Venom Cannon Weapons (Tyranid)

**Signature Rule:** ***Rending***

**Identity:** Crystallized toxin fired at high velocity. Anti-vehicle bio-weapon. The crystal shards find weak points in armor on a lucky hit. Rending (wound roll of 6 = auto-wound at AP2; pen roll of 6 = +D3) provides the anti-armor ceiling.

**Members:** Venom Cannon, Heavy Venom Cannon.

**Factions:** Tyranids.

