## NEW USRs DEFINED IN THIS GUIDE

The following USRs were created during this design session and need to be added to the OmniHammer Core Rules USR list:

### Phosphex

> ***Phosphex:*** A weapon with this special rule uses a blast marker. After resolving the initial attack, leave the blast marker in place for the remainder of the game. The marker is dangerous terrain that provides no cover.
>
> Any model that begins its turn under the marker, or moves through the marker during the Movement or Assault phases, suffers a **S5 AP3** hit with ***Ignores Cover***. A model may only suffer hits from each individual Phosphex marker once per turn. A model may suffer hits from multiple different Phosphex markers in the same turn.
>
> Against vehicles, resolve hits against the armor facing closest to the center of the marker.

### Tesla

> ***Tesla:*** When firing a weapon with this special rule, each To Hit roll of 6 generates one additional automatic hit on the target. For each bonus hit generated, roll a D6; on a further 6, another bonus hit is generated. Continue rolling until no further 6s are rolled.

### Rad-Phage

Already defined in the Imperial Knights codex:

> ***Rad-Phage:*** Models that suffer one or more unsaved wounds from a weapon with this rule have their Toughness permanently reduced by 1 for the remainder of the game (to a minimum of 1). This effect does not stack — a model's Toughness can only be reduced by 1 from Rad-Phage regardless of how many times it is wounded by Rad-Phage weapons.

### Luminagen

Already defined in the Imperial Knights codex:

> ***Luminagen:*** ***Blind***. A unit hit (regardless of wounds/armour penetration) by one or more attacks with the Luminagen special rule has its cover saves reduced by 1 (to a minimum of no cover save) until the end of the current turn. This effect does not stack with itself.

